main event: An oval, dark object was observed sliding with the wind and then disappeared from sight.
interesting points: The object was observed for 6 minutes.
The object was oval-shaped and approximately 8 feet in diameter.
The object was first observed at an altitude of 1,501 feet.
The object was sighted at 2:00 AM on January 23, 1957 near Lake Stevens, Washington.
The report concludes the object was possibly a balloon or aircraft.
